Modrow invited Gorbachev and Premier Nikolai I. He said he agreed with Gorbachev that reunification must be decided not only by East and West Germany, but all of Europe. Soviets say the question of German reunification is to be decided in the future. Modrow told reporters after the meeting that Gorbachev did not rule out such a prospect in the future, and at the same time did not venture to set some time limits for that.  Gorbachev met Tuesday with East German Premier Hans Modrow and appeared to be more open toward eventual German reunification. President Mikhail S. 